<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="754">Econ. Bot</emphasis>
. 27: 165. 1973), and Ullrich (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="754">Herbertia</emphasis>
49: 50-57. 1994), who lists many early illustrations, including a Clusius plate cited by Linnaeus, which is also reproduced by 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ramón-Laca">Ramon-Laca</normalizedToken>
(in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="754">Anales Jard. Bot. Madrid</emphasis>
57: 100. 1999).
</paragraph>
